document.title: 2023 Indiana Academic Standards: Grades 6-8 Physical Education

2E98D41E810C4D5697289B8B993E8C5C.description:
Demonstrates respect for self and others by following the rules and
encouraging others in various physical activities and games.

43CC81BF139B4309ADDCD00037E646F9.description:
Describes how moving competently in a physical activity setting creates
enjoyment.

E97E634AE45540A2886115D4AC2308E3.description:
Applies strategies for overcoming individual challenges in a physical activity
setting (such as extending effort, asking for help or feedback, or modifying the tasks).

5736D1D09F4B44F69F62CD2F7DC8D1C5.description:
Applies strategies for overcoming individual challenges in a physical activity
setting (such as extending effort, asking for help or feedback, or modifying the tasks).

BC4155C434C74C279468970B9AC00281.description:
The physically literate individual recognizes the value of physical activity for
health, enjoyment, challenge, self expression, and/or social interaction.

B5AC12E5A35B469983E9EB510ED89EB0.description:
Uses physical activity and fitness equipment appropriately and safely with
teacher guidance.

9329BB9A458146928E8F6FA33FE1C45A.description: Cooperates with a small group of classmates during physical activities.

B80986B147F74FBE8B33B2B08C218CD9.description:
Demonstrates responsibility by providing and accepting corrective feedback to
improve performance.

7B795F7004B244BEBB160DB331B8A70C.description:
Identifies rules and etiquette for physical activities, games, dance, and rhythmic
activities.

2960E3EE8CA44505843ED3309A4910E3.description:
Exhibits personal responsibility by using appropriate etiquette, demonstrating
respect for the facilities, and exhibiting safe behaviors.

2DF35E13A94D4AE9B4900E71D492B98A.description:
The physically literate individual exhibits responsible personal and social behavior
that respects self and others.

C6D1679075D841ACAD4B9B3D14279CA0.description:
Maintains and reflects on an activity log to create goals pertaining to a personal
physical activity.

D37AB9475FAE48C881AA44449AF31006.description:
Uses a SMART (specific, measurable, attainable, realistic, and timely) goal to
improve or maintain one area of health-related fitness based on a fitness assessment.

2EA3518D1D1C4C7CB9588F33F034E738.description: Compares and contrasts caloric expenditure for a variety of physical activities.

9B2510B7CCA1424BB4279AD03DA2E614.description: Identifies major muscles used in selected physical activities.

4D3E2E2E0AB045668263F1B20AD9B70D.description: Participates in a variety of cardiorespiratory endurance activities.

0D94D8A3D11A4AA8BDE536FF26E87DDC.description:
Describes the role of warm-ups and cool-downs before and after physical
activity.

5A06FCFAAF134E4F92543A5F80D1581E.description:
Describes each component of the FITT principle (frequency, intensity, time,
type) for cardiorespiratory endurance.

2640B1F341D34847A1659D3486440624.description: Uses pacing in cardiorespiratory endurance activities.

BAEDDE46ACD54E9F90E0C86ABFD52440.description: Demonstrates correct techniques and methods of stretching.

696201018CD94230B7A78D471B823A48.description: Differentiates between aerobic and anaerobic physical activity.

44D4B517FB2541A78AAA476414FCE014.description: Participates in self-selected physical activity outside of physical education class.

5435F5F168E44D52812C78695CCC4261.description: Describes how being physically active leads to a healthy body.

56833D8B32C64F5A89C6F0120DB0C1E9.description:
The physically literate individual demonstrates the knowledge and skills to
achieve and maintain a health-enhancing level of physical activity and fitness.

CBC50D40E7DF47B09FA4286FE75F8EE9.description: Developmentally appropriate outcomes first appear in grade seven.

32E99C9DC9134835AB69CABFD5CEBFD8.description: Tactics and Shots, Net and Wall Games

8624F8E5831044D3A8638221C8775282.description: Developmentally appropriate outcomes first appear in grade seven.

4C7448385A794594BFA747BA5A84A284.description: Creating Space, Net and Wall Games

B5BE0C37B86A467BB24D94C46625881D.description:
Demonstrates the transitions from offense to defense and defense to offense
by recovering quickly.

C66DA8D81F4E4F23BE445FE966A25177.description:
Identifies the correct defensive play based on the situation (such as number of
outs). (field and strike games)

1002843B242E44D39C5DB0ED384E408E.description:
Demonstrates at least one way to reduce open space (such as changing body
position; by not allowing the catch (denial); allowing the catch, but not the return pass).
(invasion games)

20D17AF2369443E7B0C45686B349C035.description:
Identifies open spaces and attempts to strike objects into the space. (field and
strike games)

F227DE00BEA4493EA1E1B0DDBA8F39E0.description:
Demonstrates at least one way to create open space (such as moving to open
space without a ball or object; using a variety of passes, pivots, and fakes; using the
give and go maneuver; using the width and length of the field/court). (invasion games)

F3E1388F068C4CD29400160E8EFE0BD5.description: Identifies appropriate decisions to ensure safety of self or others.

6096C1632AD0442DB950901C1E305495.description: Varies the application of force when performing movement activities.

3413CC32942C45D296047428BB0CDBF8.description: Developmentally appropriate outcomes first appear in grade seven.

CD32C008A11E4C27895DD7D039182216.description:
The physically literate individual applies knowledge of concepts, principles,
strategies, and tactics related to movement and performance.

FD5F13A042F94F88B6DFC74B2A5ACC23.description:
Demonstrates the ready position in defense by weight on balls of feet, arms
extended, and eyes on the midsection of the offensive player.

7A278FB1BB5144C9BDD8B2AE1A705057.description:
Demonstrates movement with the ball or object (such as dribbling) without
defensive pressure to create open space.

1038E75566AF45AAB39812A3A3B2231F.description:
Demonstrates movement without the ball or object (such as pivot, give and go,
and fakes).

30C4071EB3BD46DF8726605BCE07011C.description: Demonstrates a controlled forehand volley with mature form.

315778265E6E48A7BEBAA2F37D92B94C.description:
Demonstrates a correct underhand or overhand serve with competency, control,
and weight transfer.

73B67A0AC751416DAF381C237CA33C60.description:
Demonstrates shooting on goal with competency during a closed environment
practice.

C06A83D83BDD470C828703A998EAFDFB.description:
Demonstrates correct forehand and backhand strokes with competency while
transferring weight with correct timing.

4902BF5F9129494690BC2352F97DDDD0.description:
Demonstrates striking a stationary or moving object with competency using an
implement with force in a variety of practices (such as golf, hockey).

8F13DB6CE0B346FF99F4086A0ED17E95.description:
Demonstrates dribbling skills with dominant hand, foot, or implement with control
while moving, changing direction, and speed.

A88A1A464E8145BBBD0349B8926E258B.description:
Demonstrates a lead pass with competency, while stationary, to a moving
receiver.

D2AD5C0C1B7E4AD0B8345854EE9C9C59.description:
Demonstrates passing and receiving with hands, feet, or implement with
competency while moving, changing direction, and speed.

93DCB6578D394E7EA161FE0183A56755.description:
Demonstrates a mature catching pattern from a variety of trajectories using
different objects during practice.

264E74C6B27444FCB32555B6DEFFB392.description: Demonstrates a mature underhand or overhand motion pattern for accuracy.

9357B196CE1B44B6A6AF0BB31F0B1F8A.description:
Demonstrates correct rhythm and pattern for one of the following activities:
dance, including folk, social, creative, line, and world;jump bands; and cardio drumming.

E0C675647E3B47EEB9B8960AA82FC2D5.description: Demonstrates correct technique for basic skills in one selected outdoor activity.

B200856553934E0B9B7593BFAEE92384.description:
Demonstrates correct technique for basic skills in one selected individual
performance activity.

87FCB9D11582494B8DECF4B0D55465CC.description:
The physically literate individual will demonstrate competency in a variety of
motor skills and movement patterns.
